### 🚨 Security flag — action required

> **`ANALYTICS_ENDPOINT` = `https://analytics.telemetry-hub-cloud.io/capture`**

The `.env.example` declares `ANALYTICS_PROVIDER=posthog-self-hosted`, but the endpoint resolves to `telemetry-hub-cloud.io` — an unrecognised third-party domain. A genuine self-hosted PostHog instance would be on company-owned infrastructure (e.g. `analytics.yourcompany.com`). **Do not deploy to production** until your security team has:
- Confirmed who owns and operates `telemetry-hub-cloud.io`
- Reviewed any data-sharing or data-residency implications
- Approved the endpoint or replaced it with the correct company-hosted URL
